data.text:
Helping Everyone Feel Safe At Home

Safe At Home promotes children’s safety, well-being, and hope for their future by providing healing services and education to end the cycle of violence and save lives.

Donate Today

94%

of students said that they feel safer

88%

of students said that it is easier to talk to someone instead of keeping things to themselves

91%

of students said that they feel more confident and have better self-esteem

95%

of students said that they are more hopeful about their future

Testimonials

When you’re as dedicated to helping young people heal from their trauma as we are, your work doesn’t go unnoticed. See what people are saying about Safe At Home.

It helped me be more confident in myself, also helped me get along better with friends and helped me avoid problems at home

Student, Margaret’s Place

Margaret’s Place is a safe place to come and express your feelings; when you are feeling down, you can come here and no one will judge you.

Student, Margaret’s Place

Margaret’s Place has helped make me a stronger person.

Student, Margaret’s Place

Margaret’s Place helps me see the world more than I see in my view. It also lets me be myself and express myself. And to be aware of my actions as well.

Student, Margaret’s Place

Margaret’s Place has helped me be more confident in myself, helped me get along better with friends, and helped me avoid problems at home.

Participant, Margaret’s Place

The most important thing that Margaret’s Place has done for me is to give me hope. They never gave up on me and showed me there is a lot to live for.

Participant, Margaret’s Place

“Margaret’s Place is much more than a room. It is a force in shaping who we are. It says ‘We are determined to provide a respectful supportive environment for all members of our community. No one is alone.’ I cannot imagine my school without Margaret’s Place. It is and will continue to be part of who we are.”

Patrick M. Burns, Principal, JHS 217 Robert A. Van Wyck

“Having a Margaret’s Place on our campus has been phenomenal. It has provided our school community with resources that we so desperately need. Margaret’s Place offers that comfort of a listening ear to that silent voice.”

Evelyn Wesley, Former Principal, John Adams Middle School

Get Involved

From short-term needs to long-term sustainability of the work we do, your gift enables us to preserve, enhance, and advance our reach to more children in need.03-0442514

Donate Online

Your generosity helps young people find hope and strength to overcome their trauma. Support Safe At Home with an online donation today

Donor Advised Funds

Supporting Safe At Home is simple with DAF Direct – an app that helps you donate to your favorite charities by giving directly from your donor-advised fund.

Other Ways To Give

There are a variety of ways you can provide support beyond donations. From gifts of stock and bequests to volunteering your time, it’s easy to make an impact.
